predict_diagnosis:
1. McCune-Albright syndrome
2. Polycystic ovary syndrome (PCOS) with associated fibrous dysplasia
3. Gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) deficiency or hypothalamic amenorrhea
4. Turners syndrome with associated fibrous dysplasia
5. Endometriosis with ovarian cysts and uterine abnormalities
6. Hereditary hemorrhagic telangiectasia (HHT) with polyostotic fibrous dysplasia
7. Peutz-Jeghers syndrome with gynecological manifestations
8. Ovarian hyperthecosis leading to increased estradiol and endocrine abnormalities
9. Adenomyosis with metrorrhagia and enlarged uterus
10. Constitutional mismatch repair deficiency syndrome with gynecological and skeletal involvement.
